---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Mauritius Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mauritius/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Madagascar for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/madagascar' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'mauritiusFit', header: 'Mauritius Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR$22,500-32,140/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR$26,325-37,610/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR$20,250-28,925/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MUR$18,800-26,855/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Swan, MUA)', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'MUR$5,000-12,000/mo', mauritiusFit: 'Regional' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MUR$20,250-32,140', annual: 'MUR$243K-385.7K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MUR$27,780-42,850', annual: 'MUR$333.4K-514.2K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MUR$37,350-57,540', annual: 'MUR$448.2K-690.5K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MUR$1,500-4,000/visit', annual: 'Moderate' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MUR$8,000-20,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mauritius 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Mauritius. Tropical paradise, English-speaking, stable democracy, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mauritius"
  subheadline="Mauritius offers tropical island paradise, English as official language, stable democracy, excellent infrastructure, and welcoming retirement program—Africa's premier expat destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/mauritius-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Mauritius</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius offers tropical beauty, English as official language, stable democracy, excellent infrastructure, and dedicated retirement visa program. For retirees seeking island paradise with good healthcare and English accessibility, Mauritius is Africa's premier destination.
  </p>

  <p>
    Port Louis is the capital with main hospitals. Grand Baie offers resort lifestyle. Flic en Flac has beach living. Curepipe provides highland climate. Most expats choose coastal areas for lifestyle with easy access to Port Louis healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good private; regional backup to SA available</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English (official); French; Creole</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MUR$60,000-120,000/month (~$1,350-2,700 USD); moderate-high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; summer Nov-Apr; cyclone risk</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Multicultural; stable; tourist-friendly</li>
      <li><strong>Retirement visa:</strong> Premium Visa for retirees available</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Mauritius Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius has good healthcare for island nation—Apollo Bramwell Hospital and City Clinic provide modern private care. Public healthcare free but basic. Many doctors trained in UK, France, South Africa. Complex cases may need South Africa (4-hour flight) but most conditions treatable locally.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is good and reasonably priced. Island-wide access. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage and regional access. Better healthcare infrastructure than most African destinations.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Good Local Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Mauritius has good private healthcare for island nation. Most conditions treatable locally. South Africa provides backup for complex cases (4-hour flight). Better healthcare than most African retirement destinations. International insurance still recommended for comprehensive coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Mauritius has excellent retirement options:
  </p>

  <h3>Premium Visa (Retired Non-Citizen)</h3>
  <p>
    Dedicated retirement visa. $1,500/month income requirement. 10-year validity. Excellent option for retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Occupation Permit (Investor)</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in property ($375,000+). Leads to residence. Popular with wealthy retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    60-90 days visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For long-term settlement. Various categories with investment requirements.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Mauritius:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Premium Visa:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> South Africa coverage for complex cases</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Mauritius</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage. Local private healthcare handles most needs. South Africa provides backup for complex cases. Premium Visa requires health insurance. Good combination of local care and international backup.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Mauritius, comprehensive coverage with regional backup:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Mauritius</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong regional network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> Regional backup for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Local quality:</strong> Good private options on island</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Mauritius retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Mauritius (MUR ~45 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local private:</strong> Good quality available on island</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Use local care for routine</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Indian Ocean focused</li>
    <li><strong>Premium Visa:</strong> Requires proof of coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Premium Visa Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,500/month pension. Premium Visa. Grand Baie.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global comprehensive with UK coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MUR$25,000/month (~$555). Paradise lifestyle; global backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: South African Neighbor, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> ZAR$50,000/month pension. Property investor. Flic en Flac.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with South Africa home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MUR$32,000/month (~$710). Regional proximity; home backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: French Francophone, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month pension. Premium Visa. Curepipe highlands.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with France coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MUR$21,000/month (~$465). French language; European backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is the Premium Visa?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Dedicated retirement visa—requires $1,500/month income proof, health insurance, no criminal record. 10-year validity. Allows indefinite residence. Popular with British, French, South African retirees. Good option for serious retirement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Mauritius expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate-high—more expensive than mainland Africa. Imported goods costly. Property expensive in popular areas. Budget $1,500-3,000/month depending on lifestyle. Not cheap but good value for island paradise with infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What languages work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        English and French both work—officially English but French widely spoken. Creole is local language. Multilingual society. Healthcare available in English/French. Both colonial heritage languages functional.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about cyclones?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Real risk November-April—cyclone season brings some storms. Well-prepared country with warning systems. Modern buildings cyclone-resistant. Brief disruptions possible. Part of tropical island life; manageable risk.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Mauritius coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Mauritius authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
